The paper focuses on the application of deep reinforcement learning in human-robot cooperation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of hierarchical control and task decomposition, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves human subject experiments, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper addresses the challenges of learning in a dynamic environment, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
